# TFG Workspace (Sibling Repo)

A parallel checkout lives at `../TFG/` (same parent: `ProteinDesign/`). Same scientific project; different directory layout and local state.

## Which repo am I in?

| | `alzheimer-peptide-design/` | `TFG/` |
|--|------------------------------|--------|
| Layout | `packages/{dataset,bbb_models,...}` | Flat `{dataset,bbb_models,...}` |
| Git name | `alzheimer-peptide-design` | `gsk3b-peptide-design` |
| CI / pre-commit | Yes (`Makefile`, `.github/workflows/ci.yml`) | Minimal dev deps |
| Docs | `docs/architecture/`, `docs/models/` | Flat `docs/*.md` |
| Local artifacts | Usually absent (gitignored) | Often present (`bbb_models/artifacts/`, trained exp09) |
| Thesis deliverables | — | `entregas/` (local only, not committed) |

**Prefer `alzheimer-peptide-design/` for new code, CI, and GitHub.** Use `TFG/` when you need local trained checkpoints, active Vast instance state, or thesis outputs.

## Path mapping

| TFG | alzheimer-peptide-design |
|-----|--------------------------|
| `TFG/bbb_models/` | `packages/bbb_models/` |
| `TFG/dataset/` | `packages/dataset/` |
| `TFG/boltzgen_design/` | `packages/boltzgen_design/` |
| `TFG/boltzgen/` | `packages/boltzgen/` |
| `TFG/docs/AGENT_CONTEXT.md` | `docs/architecture/agent-context.md` |
| `TFG/docs/VAST_TRAINING.md` | `docs/infrastructure/vast-training.md` |
| `TFG/docs/STRUCTURAL_BBB_GUIDANCE.md` | `docs/models/structural-bbb-guidance.md` |

When docs or scripts still say `TFG/`, translate to `packages/` (or repo root) in the canonical repo.

## Vast.ai differences

**TFG** — `boltzgen_design/scripts/vast/_common.sh` uses hardcoded `VAST_SSH_HOST`/`PORT`; remote root `/workspace/TFG`.

**Canonical repo** — shared helpers in `infra/vast/_common.sh`; dynamic SSH via `vastai show instance`; remote root `/workspace/alzheimer-peptide-design`.

Guided campaign flow (canonical repo):

```bash
bash infra/vast/boltzgen_design/launch.sh <INSTANCE_ID>
bash infra/vast/boltzgen_design/setup_guided_env.sh <INSTANCE_ID>
SMOKE=1 bash infra/vast/boltzgen_design/run_guided_campaign.sh <INSTANCE_ID>
bash infra/vast/boltzgen_design/sync_results.sh <INSTANCE_ID>
```

GSK3β target files: `boltzgen_design/targets/gsk3b/` (`gsk3b.cif`, `gsk3b_peptide_design.yaml`, `guidance_feats.json`).
